fields.description:
Some AccessDenied error responses from s3 put the error message in the resource element:

{code}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Error><Code>AccessDenied</Code><Message>Access Denied</Message><Resource>X-Amz-Date parameter must be specified.</Resource><RequestId>e16d580d-1176-4120-8071-f3d73f9e6c90</RequestId></Error>
{code}

The resource should be the object or bucket, not the error message:

{quote}
Resource 	The bucket or object that is involved in the error.
{quote}

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/ErrorResponses.html

comments.body:
Since the signature validation error is now:

{code}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Error><Code>SignatureDoesNotMatch</Code><Message>The request signature we calculated does not match the signature you provided.</Message><Resource></Resource><RequestId>b3b5d51c-6095-4008-8268-68fcd9ba0fcd</RequestId></Error>
{code}

it no longer has information to help the caller determine what they may have done incorrectly when signing the request. Note that this impacts v2 signatures as well as v4.

From code review it looks like this change may also have removed the access key id from InvalidAccessKeyId error responses and impacted propagation of some error messages from a walrus backend.
